{title:CLIPPOLYGON (beta release)}

{p 4 4 2}
{cmd:clippolygon} takes a polygon shapefile and clips it on a manually defined bounding box. The program implements the {browse "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sutherland%E2%80%93Hodgman_algorithm":Sutherlandâ€“Hodgman} algorithm. 


{marker syntax}{title:Syntax}
{p 8 15 2}
{cmd:clippolygon} {it:filename}, [{cmdab:b:ox}({it:x_min x_max y_min y_max})]


{synoptset 36 tabbed}{...}
{synopthdr}
{synoptline}
{p2coldent : {it:filename}}is the {it:*_shp.dta} file generated by Stata that contains polygon coordinates.{p_end}

{p2coldent : {opt b:ox(x_min x_max y_min y_max)}}The bounding box coordinates need to be specified in the correct order.{p_end}
